Application.Controller

Class FeedController

  • java.lang.Object
    • Application.Controller.FeedController

  • @SessionAttributes(value={"limit","scenarioId"})
 @Controller
public class FeedController
extends java.lang.Object
    Controller class for managing the page with all the Vision(s). The feed page contains the most recent Vision(s) shared on the platform by the User(s). From there, it is also possible to visit the profile of other User(s) and start a new Match.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Corti Lorenzo, Tocchetti Andrea

    • Method Detail

      • getFeed

        @RequestMapping(value="/feed",
                method={GET,POST})
public java.lang.String getFeed(org.springframework.ui.Model model,
                                                                                                  @CookieValue(value="user_id",defaultValue="NULL")
                                                                                                  java.lang.String user_id,
                                                                                                  @RequestParam(name="limit",required=false,defaultValue="0")
                                                                                                  int limit,
                                                                                                  @RequestParam(name="scenarioId",required=false,defaultValue="0")
                                                                                                  int scenarioId)
        Returns the page containing all the Vision(s) shared by the User(s) within the Scenario. Only a fixed amount of Vision(s) are loaded by default. The page is only accessible after all the other activities have been carried out.
        Parameters:
        model - Spring Model object.
        user_id - The unique identifier of the User.
        limit - The fixed amount of Vision(s) loaded.
        scenarioId - The unique identifier of the Scenario.
        Returns:
        "feed" string indicating the name of the Thymeleaf template to parse and return to the client.
